messages.message: Hey Team, when GCS is configured as datasource, upstream and downstream integration with storage, breaks on file open operation. Open button just hangs at the end. I didn't see anything evident in console and of course on the network tab. I tried to do event based break point walkthrough, but couldn't capture the last one may be because, she clicked through the step over little faster(?) I have attached the HAR and video(kept the playback speed 1.5x) for the reference. This is happening on Kering.aihub.instabase.com (http://Kering.aihub.instabase.com)
I think it's working. The file is indeed selected, but the user needs to close the file picker. Probably a bug on how we integrate file picker in this particular use case
As you can see from the recording, the `path to input folder` input is indeed populated
